<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In other Marina tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 71, El Dorado 63 (OT) -- Sixth-ranked Fountain Valley (9-4) 
made only 34% of its shots in regulation, but made six of seven in overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 Seventh-ranked El Dorado (7-2) led, 49-42, with 4:02 left, but made only one 
more field goal -- Shannon Nebeker's basket with three seconds left -- to force 
overtime. The Golden Hawks committed four turnovers in the last 2:20, and 
committed three more in overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 Shanna Renken had a game-high 33 points and 18 rebounds for El Dorado. 
Fountain Valley got 20 points from Jennifer Ludwicki and 12 apiece from Jocelyn 
Tu and Saki Takemoto. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina 52, Ocean View 34 -- Fifth-ranked Marina (10-1) got 17 points from 
Sonya Bryant and 10 from Shandy Robbins to beat Ocean View (6-6). Becky Fraser 
had 14 points for the Seahawks. 
</P>
<P>
 In consolation games: 
</P>
<P>
 Coney (Me.) 72, Loara 31 -- Paola Flores scored 12 for Loara (3-7). Becky 
Joosten added nine and 11 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Lakewood 46, Mission Viejo 45 (OT) -- Erika Burton's basket at the buzzer was 
first disallowed by officials -- and then allowed after a discussion -- to pin 
an overtime loss on Mission Viejo (6-5). Shelly Higham had a team-high 20 
points for Mission Viejo, and Kortney Okura had 11. 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego Morse 70, La Quinta 30 -- La Quinta (0-10) fell behind, 19-6, and 
never recovered. Tina Shum scored 12 points. 
</P>
<P>
 In pool play of the Cavalier Classic: 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 46, El Modena 31 -- Jennie Wallace scored 13 points and grabbed 11 
rebounds and Nadia Hoerner had 13 points and 14 rebounds for Fullerton (6-5), 
which plays Edison tonight at 8. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Costa Mesa Tournament 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 47, San Luis Obispo 36 -- Jennifer Garrett had 21 points and 
21 rebounds to lead Capistrano Valley (8-3), which plays Montebello Schurr for 
fifth place today at 4:30. 
</P>
<P>
 Kirkland (Wash.) Lake Washington 57, Costa Mesa 55 -- Costa Mesa (7-4) led by 
six points with less than two minutes remaining but couldn't stop Sarah 
Yarbrough (21 points). Corri Lurmann led Costa Mesa with 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 45, Westminster 39 -- Kelly Grant scored 17 points for San 
Clemente (8-6), which plays Long Beach Jordan today at 3 in the consolation 
championship. 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 79, North Torrance 38 -- Katie Scheuerman led Tustin (7-7) with 20 
points and made two three-pointers to give her 100 in her career. Alison Carr 
added 16 for the Tillers. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 70, Huntington Beach 50 -- No. 1 Woodbridge (12-0) was led by Erin 
Stovall's 18 points, and Angela Burgess' 19-point, 13-rebound effort. The 
Warriors play Kirkland Lake Washington in the finals tonight at 7:30. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Garden Grove tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia 62, Rancho Alamitos 35 -- Andrea Picchi scored 24 points and had 19 
rebounds for Magnolia (8-3). Sophia Garcia had a career-high 17 points for the 
Sentinels. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Laguna Beach tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Century 51, Calvary Chapel 38 -- Ashleigh Griset scored 15 to lead Century 
(7-3) into the finals tonight at 7:30 against Trabuco Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills 44, Laguna Hills 41 (OT) -- LaShieka Henderson scored seven of 
the Mustangs' nine points in overtime. Henderson had 15 points and Dyanna Hatch 
13 to lead Trabuco Hills (11-3). Laguna Hills (9-3) played without 6-5 center 
Tayyiba Haneef, but got 13 points from Tamara Inoue. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 41, Brethren Christian 40 -- April Chambers scored 20 points for 
Laguna Beach (2-8), which plays Orange Lutheran today in the consolation 
championship at 4:30. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran 57, Irvine 55 -- Liz Pappas and Michelle Morales each scored 
14 points to lead Orange Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Santiago tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 66, Sonora 57 -- Jennifer Gardner scored 23 points to lead 
Corona del Mar (5-7) in pool play. Aiyana Nash had 36 points for Sonora (3-8). 
</P>
<P>
 In second round of the Savanna tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 55, Brock (Canada) 39 -- Brook Koehler scored 12 points and Amy Lien 
added 11 to lead La Habra (6-5). 
</P>
<P>
 La Mirada 27, Los Amigos 17 -- Camela Zavala scored seven points for Los 
Amigos (4-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana 73, Los Alamitos 45 -- Letty Gil scored 22 points and handed out 12 
assists to pace Santa Ana (7-4). Tanzenika Holmes added 20 points for the 
Saints. 
</P>
<P>
 Savanna 30, Cypress 29 -- Shannon Pendergraft scored 17 points and Shauna 
Miller added seven to lead Savanna (4-6). 
</P>
