<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In other Orange tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 73, Marina 45 -- Gordon Orsborn scored 17 points and Kurt Nelson 
added 14 for Laguna Beach (6-6) in a consolation game. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 41, Valencia 32 -- Andy Lauridsen scored 13 points for Orange (4-6), 
which led 28-13 at halftime in a consolation game. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran 67, Aliso Niguel 57 -- Sonny Madsen scored 19 points and Armen 
Bagatourian added 14 for Orange Lutheran (3-7) in a consolation game. Tim 
Blagassa scored 15 points for Aliso Niguel (4-8). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Reebok/Above the Rim tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 93, Merced 48 -- Mater Dei's competition is getting easier and the 
Monarchs' play keeps getting better. The result was a blowout in the 
quarterfinals at Torrey Pines High in Del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
 After receiving a scare in the first round against San Diego Scripps Ranch, 
the top-ranked Monarchs (14-1) have had two consecutive laughers. Wednesday's 
game, played before a crowd of about 2,000 that included Jerry Tarkanian, was 
close for about five minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei led Merced (8-5) by three points before going on a 29-7 run the 
final 11 minutes of the half. Senior guard Clay McKnight was the spark as he 
hit five three-pointers in the half, and finished with six three-pointers on 11 
attempts and 20 points after scoring only six Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore forward Schea Cotton had his second consecutive spectacular game, 
scoring 28 points on a wide array of rim-rattling dunks and pretty inside 
moves. About the only area Cotton didn't dominate was on the perimeter, where 
he was one of five from three-point range. He made 10 of 16 shots overall and 
grabbed six rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Center Shaun Jackson added 20 points, 10 rebounds, three blocks and three 
assists. Point guard Kevin Augustine was the only Monarch who didn't play well, 
scoring just three points and committing eight turnovers in 20 minutes of play. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei will play Queens (N.Y.) Christ the King (6-1) in tonight's 
semifinals at 7:30. Christ the King is led by 6-6 junior forward Ira Miller, 
who scored 17 points and grabbed 11 rebounds in Wednesday's 73-69 quarterfinal 
victory over Riverside North. DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
