<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' SOCCER ROUNDUP; HULGREEN'S GOAL PUTS MATER DEI IN MARINA TITLE GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kris Hulgreen scored off a pass from Matt Thomas early in the second half to 
give Mater Dei a 1-0 victory over San Clemente Wednesday and move the Monarchs 
into the championship game of the Marina boys' soccer tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 The Monarchs, who defeated Santa Barbara San Marcos, 2-1, earlier Wednesday, 
will face Clovis West in today's final at 1:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 In the other semifinal: 
</P>
<P>
 Clovis West 1, Fountain Valley 0 -- Jim Smith scored a first-half 
goal.Second-ranked Fountain Valley (9-2), which defeated Long Beach Wilson, 
4-0, in the quarterfinals, will play San Clemente for third place today at 
10:30 a.m. at Marina. 
</P>
<P>
 In the quarterfinals of the Orange tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 2, Edison 0 -- Juan Rojas and Oswaldo Vis each scored to lead 
Saddleback (5-2-1). Eddy Lopez posted the shutout for the Roadrunners, who play 
North Riverside in a 6:45 p.m. semifinal today at Chapman University. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 2, La Habra 1 -- Victor Diaz's goal proved the difference for Orange 
(5-4-2), which will face Santa Margarita, top-ranked in Orange County, in the 
semifinals today at 5 p.m. at Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 1, Los Alamitos 0 -- Seth George scored in the second half to 
get Santa Margarita past fourth-ranked Los Alamitos. Ben Froehlich had six 
saves in the shutout. 
</P>
<P>
 In a consolation game: 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia 1, Trabuco Hills 0 -- Garrison Sagado scored a second-half goal to 
lead Estancia (4-2-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 3, Magnolia 2 -- Brad Dunaway scored twice and Mike Gaitley added 
another goal to lead Cypress (9-2-2). Bryce Brunsting had three saves for 
Cypress. 
</P>
