<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; SECOND-HALF RALLY LIFTS SCC TO VICTORY OVER GRACELAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Kostoff and Chauncey Woolridge each scored 22 points as Southern 
California College edged Graceland, 98-91, in a nonconference men's basketball 
game Wednesday in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 SCC was down by five points at halftime, but outscored Graceland, 49-37, in 
the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Kostoff also had 11 rebounds and Kevin Carlson scored 20 points for SCC (7-7). 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonconference men's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Idaho State 73, Chapman 52 -- The Division I Bengals (7-1) used a 19-6 run in 
the second half to pull away from the Division III Panthers (6-4) in the 
Gossner Foods Classic in Logan, Utah. Chapman was led by Stefan Mumaw with 16 
points and 11 rebounds. Adam Dzierzynski added 12 points for the Panthers. 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia 90, Malone College 71 -- Pharoh Jones scored 20 points and grabbed 
11 rebounds and Craig Martin had 19 points and 13 rebounds to lead Concordia 
(9-1). Martin made eight of 10 shots and all three of his three-point attempts. 
</P>
<P>
 In the UCSD women's basketball Invitational: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 84, Elmira 66 -- Melody Earle scored 24 points to lead Chapman (5-3) 
in the first-round game at the University of San Diego. Earle also had eight 
rebounds and Monique Sweet added 10 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Martha Bolduc had 21 points and 10 rebounds for Elmira (2-6). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's basketball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia 96, Occidental 54 -- Concordia took a 53-27 halftime lead and never 
let up against visiting Occidental. Kara Stephens and Jennifer Zylstra had 13 
points each to lead Concordia (7-5). 
</P>
<P>
 USC 84, Long Beach State 61 -- Tina Thompson made 10 of 12 free throws and 
scored 24 points to lead USC. 
</P>
<P>
 The Trojans (6-1) played tough defense and forced 40 turnovers by Long Beach 
State (2-4). 
</P>
