<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; VENTURA TOPPLES CERRITOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Forward Hakeem Ward scored 18 points and grabbed 12 rebounds to lead Ventura 
College, the state's top-ranked team, to a convincing 87-62 victory over 
third-ranked Cerritos College in a semifinal game of the John Hancock 
tournament Wednesday.  
</P>
<P>
 "Our goal was to keep them off the offensive glass," Ventura Coach Philip 
Mathews said.  
</P>
<P>
 "We were just the better team tonight. They didn't play well, but I think we 
had something to do with that." 
</P>
<P>
 Five players scored in double figures for the Pirates (17-0), including guards 
Shannon Taylor, who scored 17, and Jamal Cobbs, who contributed 15 points and 
eight assists. 
</P>
<P>
 "We like to play an up-tempo game and we like to press," Matthews said.  
</P>
<P>
 "But we can play any type of game people throw at us." 
</P>
<P>
 Leading by six, Ventura, which didn't trail, put the Falcons (18-1) away with 
a 20-0 run with 12 minutes left. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura, which forced 21 turnovers, stole eight passes, with Ward, Cobb and 
Jason Fay each snaring two. 
</P>
<P>
 "We played man-to-man defense the whole time and put a lot of pressure on 
them," Mathews said.  
</P>
<P>
 "We just wore them down."  
</P>
<P>
 Ventura will play Irvine Valley in the championship game tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 In other men's games: 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 85, Moorpark 83 -- The Marauders upset the tournament 
defending champions when Orville Turner (22 points, 10 rebounds) hit a layup 
with one second left in the semifinals of the College of the Canyons 
tournament.  
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark's Nick Foster missed a four-foot jumper in the final second, sending 
Antelope Valley to tonight's final. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley guard Brandon McIntire made five of seven three-point 
attempts, and wound up with 15 points.  
</P>
<P>
 Nick Foster finished with 25 points and 12 rebounds for the Raiders.  
</P>
<P>
 Twin brother Paul Foster fouled out with five minutes left after scoring 14 
points and getting 11 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons 68, El Camino 53 -- The host Cougars outscored El Camino in the first 
half, 39-24. 
</P>
<P>
 Rashe Dorsey had 12 points and 11 rebounds and Kwesi Fulton contributed 15 
points and 14 rebounds.  
</P>
<P>
 Canyons will face Antelope Valley in tonight's 8 p.m. championship game. WOMEN 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 81, Antelope Valley 52 -- Playing against some familiar faces, Monarch 
forward Erika Kusek scored 18 points, making eight of 13 shots from the field, 
in the consolation quarterfinal round of the Fullerton tournament.  
</P>
<P>
 The freshman from Quartz Hill High hit four three-point shots and had four 
assists and two steals. 
</P>
<P>
 Yvonne Zandi had 15 points and 16 rebounds and Erika Upton had 10 points and 
12 rebounds for Valley (10-5). 
</P>
</TEXT>
