<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL / HART TOURNAMENT; CANYON FLOATS PAST UNDERMANNED VENICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BRESNAHAN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Instead of waiting around for last-second heroics, as the Cowboys did in a 
first-round victory over Antelope Valley, Canyon exploded in the third quarter 
to beat Venice, 89-65, in the quarterfinals of the Hart tournament Wednesday at 
Valencia High. 
</P>
<P>
 Greg Minor scored 38 points and sparked a 14-2 run to start the third quarter, 
and Canyon advanced to the tournament semifinals, where it will face Hart. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon broke a 37-37 halftime tie by outscoring Venice, 26-7, in the third 
quarter. Venice (6-5) suited up only six players and was led by Charles 
Madison's 23 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Connelly added 14 points for Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart 57, Beverly Hills 45 -- Mike Posey scored 15 points and Zach Koebel added 
12 to lead the tournament host Indians (7-5) in another quarterfinal. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 87, Palmdale 73 -- Anthony Tauriello scored 23 points to lead Simi 
Valley (9-1) in a quarterfinal game. The Pioneers will meet Notre Dame tonight. 
Shad Martin led Palmdale with 19 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame 67, Glendale 55 -- The Knights (8-3) sank 12 of 14 free throws in 
the fourth quarter, pulling away in a quarterfinal game. Notre Dame's Tom 
Zapata finished with 12 points. Arnae Boghossian led Glendale (7-4) with 28 
points. 
</P>
<P>
 Littlerock 56, Banning 54 -- John George hit a 10-foot jumper at the buzzer 
for Littlerock in a consolation game. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Lonien scored a season high 22 points for Littlerock (7-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Atwater 81, Canoga Park 80 -- Cesar Lopez missed a short jump shot and Canoga 
Park fell in a consolation game. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Harper scored 21 points and had 10 rebounds for Canoga Park (4-5). 
</P>
</TEXT>
