<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; NORTH HOLLYWOOD ADVANCES TO BELL-JEFF FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 North Hollywood High used a balanced offense to dismantle Rosamond, 78-41, in 
a semifinal of the Bell-Jeff tournament Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Anna Celaya, twin Bobbie Celaya and Samantha Fargeon each scored 19 points, 
while Julie Wasserman added 11 for the Huskies (8-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Burroughs 66, St. Mary's 58 -- Janelle Simon scored 20 points and grabbed 20 
rebounds, while Suzy Babko added 24 points for the Indians (5-7) in a semifinal 
of the Bell-Jeff tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Alemany 62, San Francisco Aragon 16 -- Carly Funicello scored 13 points and 
Kelly McKay added 11 as the Indians overwhelmed Aragon in the first round of 
the Surf 'N Slam tournament in La Jolla. 
</P>
<P>
 Washington Auburn 58, Buena 54 -- The Bulldogs (2-2) fell in the first round 
of the Surf 'N Slam tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Rio Mesa 44, Village Christian 42 -- Brianna Kanongata'a scored 17 points to 
lead the Spartans to a seventh-place overtime semifinal victory in the Thousand 
Oaks tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Palmdale 66, Santa Maria 46 -- Kristi Rose scored 18 points and Monique Nolan 
added 14 as the Falcons won a Thousand Oaks tournament seventh-place semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 Oak Park 79, Flintridge Sacred Heart 45 -- Natalie Davis had 25 points and 
nine rebounds for Oak Park in a consolation semifinal of the Bell-Jeff 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Grant 70, Wilson 24 -- Bahaneh Maani scored 29 points as Grant won a 
consolation game in the Birmingham tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake 50, Camarillo 43 -- Katie Spayde scored 24 points for the Warriors 
(5-8) in the consolation bracket of the Thousand Oaks tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 El Camino Real 45, Fairfax 31 -- Junior guard Tami Jones scored 34 points to 
lead the Conquistadores (3-5) in the consolation bracket of the Birmingham 
tournament. 
</P>
