<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; SAFETY: FREE RIDES OFFERED TO REVELERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Westside party-goers will be offered free transportation on New Year's Eve to 
avoid drinking and driving. 
</P>
<P>
 The shuttle service, provided by PrimeTime Shuttle International and organized 
by Mothers Against Drunk Driving (MADD), will be available for revelers who 
have been drinking. The service will be offered throughout Ventura, Los Angeles 
and Orange counties.. 
</P>
<P>
 "We don't want anyone on the road to be at risk from a drunk driver," 
PrimeTime spokesman Mike Kaliczak said. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, or to schedule a pickup, call (800) RED-VANS. 
</P>
