<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; VOLUNTEERS: BOYS SEEK BIG BROTHERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Catholic Big Brothers, a nonprofit agency affiliated with United Way, is in 
need of volunteers for its mentor program. 
</P>
<P>
 As a Big Brother, volunteers are expected to spend three to four hours a week 
with boys ages 7 to 14 who are from single-parent families or who are in need 
of positive male role models. 
</P>
<P>
 There are about 200 youths throughout Los Angeles County waiting to be 
assigned to a Big Brother. Volunteers may be of any religious affiliation. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call: (213) 251-9800. 
</P>
