<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTY TO PICK UP CHRISTMAS TREES FOR RECYCLING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In what has become a post-holiday tradition, the Ventura County Solid Waste 
Management Department will be picking up Christmas trees in the next few weeks 
for recycling. 
</P>
<P>
 Before recycling the tree, residents should carefully remove all ornaments, 
nails, tinsel, metal support rods and tree stands. Flocked or fireproofed trees 
cannot be accepted for recycling. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents with yard debris collection can put their tree into their yard 
debris barrel at any time, county officials said. In addition, curbside 
collection and drop-off locations will be available in various communities. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year the county collected 80,000 trees, which were recycled into garden 
mulch, according to county officials. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bell Canyon: Curbside Jan. 4. 
</P>
<P>
 * Camarillo: Curbside Jan. 9. Apartment complexes by appointment. 
</P>
<P>
 * Channel Islands Beach: Curbside through Jan. 6. Or drop off at 353 Santa 
Monica Drive, through Jan. 21. 
</P>
<P>
 * Moorpark: Curbside Jan. 2-13. 
</P>
<P>
 * Fillmore: Cut tree into three-foot lengths and place inside or next to yard 
debris barrel on Jan. 6 and 20 or drop off at Mountain View and Main Street. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ojai and upper Ojai Valley: Place tree inside of or next to yard debris 
barrel on the normal collection day through Jan. 6. 
</P>
<P>
 * Oxnard: Curbside through Jan. 13. 
</P>
<P>
 * Port Hueneme: Curbside through Jan. 13. 
</P>
<P>
 * Point Mugu: Curbside Jan. 9-10; Camarillo Housing, Jan. 6. 
</P>
<P>
 * Santa Paula: Curbside through Jan. 13. 
</P>
<P>
 * Simi Valley: Place tree inside or next to yard debris barrel at the curb on 
the normal refuse collection day. 
</P>
<P>
 * Susana Knolls: Curbside through Jan. 2 ($3 charge for this recycling 
service). 
</P>
<P>
 * Thousand Oaks: Drop-off centers will be open through Jan. 8 at Borchard Park 
Service Center at 250 Reino Road, Newbury Park; Triunfo Community Park, 980 
Aranmoor Ave., Westlake Village; Cal Lutheran University, Mount Clef Boulevard 
and Lynn Road; Home Depot, 500 N. Ventu Road, Newbury Park; Park & Ride at 
Janss Road and the Moorpark Freeway; and Park & Ride, Rancho Road at Ventura 
Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ventura: Apartment complexes by appointment. Place tree inside of or next to 
yard debris barrel on yard debris collection day through Jan. 6. Apartment 
complexes by appointment. 
</P>
<P>
 * Unincorporated Ventura County: Place tree in yard debris barrel and set out 
on the normal yard debris collection day. Call your hauler for information on 
special pickups. 
</P>
<P>
 * Free drop-off locations: Ojai Valley Recycling Center at Old Baldwin Road 
between 8 a.m. and 4 p.m., through Saturday; or Simi Valley Landfill at 2801 
Madera Road through Friday from 7 a.m. to 5 p.m.; Saturday 7 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. 
and Sunday 10 a.m. to 4 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 Free mulch will be available at the Ojai Valley Recycling Center, Simi Valley 
Landfill and California Wood Recycling at 3450-A Auto Center off Johnson Drive, 
Ventura, through Jan. 23. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
