<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: PROFESSIONAL SINGER TO HEAD SYMPHONY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL ELIAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County Symphony officials have hired a professional singer as their 
new executive director. 
</P>
<P>
 Patricia Hesselbach, 39, will assume the symphony's top post Tuesday, 
officials said.She replaces Karine Beesley, who resigned earlier this year. 
</P>
<P>
 In the job, she will oversee a staff of four employees and administer an 
annual budget of $730,000. She will also be in charge of fund-raising for the 
33-year-old symphony. 
</P>
<P>
 Felice Ginsberg, president of the symphony's board of directors, said 
Hesselbach was chosen from among 30 applicants.  
</P>
<P>
 Ginsberg declined to give Hesselbach's salary, but Beesley cited a wage freeze 
on her $38,900 annual salary as a factor in her resignation. 
</P>
<P>
 In recent years, the 60-member symphony has run into serious financial 
difficulties. It began the fiscal year with a $180,000 deficit, and its 
financial woes were compounded when the symphony's musicians sought a 
collective bargaining agreement for the first time.  
</P>
<P>
 But Ginsberg said Hesselbach, who now lives in San Pedro, has a combination of 
arts and business experience that should help her get through any rough spots. 
</P>
<P>
 The symphony needs to raise $150,000 next year to get a matching federal grant 
of $50,000. In addition, a permanent contract must still be signed by the 
musicians, who agreed to an interim contract weeks before the season opener. 
</P>
<P>
 Hesselbach's last related job was two years ago when she held management 
positions with the Da Camera Society of Mount St. Mary's College in Los 
Angeles. The Da Camera Society presents chamber music concerts in historic 
locations around Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Since then, Hesselbach said, she has been a free-lance public relations 
worker. She is a University of Redlands graduate with a bachelor of science 
degree in business and has worked as a professional choral singer. PAUL ELIAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
