<P>
OBITUARIES ; TONY J. HERNANDEZ; FORMER SANTA PAULA PLANNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tony J. Hernandez, a Ventura County resident for 75 years and a former Santa 
Paula planning commissioner, died Wednesday at his Santa Paula home after an 
extended illness.He was 79. 
</P>
<P>
 A retired construction laborer, Hernandez was an avid golfer and a member of 
several local service clubs. He is survived by his wife, Louisa S. Hernandez, 
six children, 16 grandchildren and 18 great-grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
 Prayer services will be held at 7 p.m. today at Pierce Brothers Stetler 
Mortuary, and Mass will be said at 9 a.m. Friday at St. Sebastian Catholic 
Church.  
</P>
<P>
 Burial will follow at Santa Paula Cemetery. 
</P>
