<TEXT>
<P>
 The game at Tucson between No. 22 Brigham Young (9-3) and Oklahoma (6-5) is 
about an arrival, a departure and a possible departure. 
</P>
<P>
 The new face on the scene is Oklahoma quarterback Terence Brown, a sophomore 
who hasn't taken a snap in a game since Oct. 22.He gets the start because 
Garrick McGee is too weak to play after a bout with meningitis. 
</P>
