<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE BOWLS DAILY REPORT; HOLIDAY / MICHIGAN VS. COLORADO STATE, FRIDAY; WHEATLEY 
NO BETTER AND NO WORSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELLIOTT ALMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After the big buildup for his senior season, Michigan's big-play running back 
Tyrone Wheatley could only equal last season's statistics. 
</P>
<P>
 And that's the odd thing. He rushed for 1,064 yards and 11 touchdowns each 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 Wheatley might have surpassed last season's total had he not missed Michigan's 
first two games because of a leg injury. Still, he was not disappointed with 
the outcome. 
</P>
<P>
 "Not to sound cocky, I like odds, I like to overcome them," he said. "I'm 
happy. A lot of guys couldn't even wear my shoes (considering) what I've been 
through. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm on course, I followed the road and I did everything I was supposed to. I 
didn't leave any rocks unturned." ELLIOTT ALMOND 
