TIMES ALL-AREA TENNIS TEAM / PLAYER OF THE YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Julia Feldman 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Taft 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: The three-year varsity performer who played No. 1 singles 
the past two seasons finished 21-0 and won the City Section singles 
championship. A powerful and athletic serve-and-volley player, Feldman finished 
48-2 at Taft. Feldman upset defending champion Kendra Segura of Dorsey, 6-4, 
6-0, for the the title that had eluded her the two previous seasons. Feldman's 
losses came in the 1993 City semifinals to Segura and the 1992 final to former 
teammate Brahna Pastorini. "I wanted this really bad," Feldman said. "I've been 
wanting to win this for the last three years." 
</P>
