Section tournament two years in a row and was chosen Marmonte League MVP. 
Darian Chappell, Camarillo, So., was 29-4, 21-0 while leading the Scorpions to 
the Marmonte League championship. Kristin Dickey, La Reina, Fr., finished 33-3 
and was the only Regent to sweep three sets in a victory over Nordhoff for the 
Southern Section Division V championship. Helena Horack, Westlake, Fr., 
finished 51-11, recording 11 sweeps in 17 matches, and was All-Marmonte League. 
Jessica Improta, Rio Mesa, Sr., had a 36-7 record and was All-Channel League 
three times. Ravid Levy, Taft, Sr., helped the Toreadors win the 1993 City 
Section championship and had a 30-0 regular-season record over the past two 
years: 18-0 in singles, 12-0 in doubles. Romy Mehlman, Harvard-Westlake, Sr., 
went 41-4 this fall, winning 29 sets by 6-0 scores. Deborah Pepkowitz, 
Calabasas, So., carried a 51-9 record while the Coyotes played one of the 
toughest schedules in the area. Zuzana Stunova, Rio Mesa, So., an exchange 
student from the Czech Republic, finished 36-3 and reached the quarterfinals of 
the Southern Section tournament, where she lost to No. 1-seeded and eventual 
champion Amanda Basica. Shera Weigler, Calabasas, Jr., amassed a 53-7 record 
and was MVP of the Sunshine League. 
