<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LITTLE BIT OF HISTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tim Foli, a 1968 graduate of Notre Dame High, batted .333 with three runs 
batted in to help the Pittsburgh Pirates beat the Baltimore Orioles in seven 
games in the 1979 World Series.  
</P>
<P>
 Foli, a baseball, football and basketball standout in high school, batted .562 
as a senior at Notre Dame. He was the first pick in baseball's amateur draft 
that year by the New York Mets, and finished with a .251 average and 15 homers 
in his 16-year major league career. 
</P>
