<P>
POMONA CARD CLUB TALKS PUT ON HOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city of Pomona has been temporarily barred from entering into agreements 
with card club developers while Los Angeles Superior Court Judge Diane Wayne 
decides whether to make her ruling permanent. 
</P>
<P>
 On Dec. 12, Wayne issued a temporary restraining order that blocked the city 
from signing card club licenses.Six days later, the council approved a license 
agreement with Champs, one of the casino developers, but was unable to finalize 
the agreement because of the ban. 
</P>
<P>
 On Tuesday, Wayne issued an injunction that appears to block the city from 
taking any further action on the card clubs, said Pomona City Atty. Arnold M. 
Alvarez-Glasman. As a result, the agreement with Champs, as well as a council 
decision on the proposed Tradewinds casino, are on hold until Jan. 20, when 
Wayne is scheduled to make a final decision. 
