<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE BLOTTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA O'NEILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ALTADENA: Members of the sheriff's bomb squad safely detonated a pipe bomb 
found Monday in a wash near a home. A man hiking about 5:10 p.m. found a tote 
bag, carried the bag to a friend's nearby house in the 500 block of Villa 
Zanita Street and found what looked like a bomb.Investigators confirmed that it 
was a bomb and blew it up in a nearby open area.  
</P>
<P>
 ALTADENA: A 23-year-old Altadena man was critically wounded Monday when he was 
shot while in his car. The man, whose name was not released, was shot about 2 
p.m. in the 600 block of Ventura Street. He was shot at least twice in the 
upper body and was taken to a local hospital, sheriff's deputies said. 
Investigators had no one in custody and did not know if the shooting was 
gang-related. 
</P>
<P>
 WEST COVINA: A 44-year-old Tennessee man was arrested Friday morning after 
allegedly firing several shotgun blasts into a state employment office and at 
passing cars. Frederick Kunz was arrested on suspicion of assault with a deadly 
weapon, shooting at an inhabited dwelling and shooting at a moving vehicle. The 
incident occurred about 7:30 a.m. Police said Kunz, who uses a wheelchair, 
apparently was disgruntled about not receiving disability benefits. Kunz had 
moved to California from Tennessee, and reportedly had an appointment for later 
that morning at the employment office. LISA O'NEILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
