<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT LOGS 218 GANG KILLINGS IN 1994 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A record 218 gang killings occurred in 1994 in areas patrolled by the Los 
Angeles County Sheriff's Department, erasing the record of 207 set in 1991, 
Sheriff Sherman Block said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Latino gang killings were up and constituted about 75% of all such killings, 
Block said. Gang murders among black youths dropped to 50, he said. The sheriff 
added that drive-by shootings have declined in the areas deputies patrol, which 
include the unincorporated county and several municipalities that contract with 
the department. 
</P>
<P>
 "Most of the gang homicides today seem to be more focused," Block said. 
"They're literally walk-up shootings, rather than drive-by shootings." 
</P>
