<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: TUSTIN; DISTRICT TO OFFER PARENTING COURSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Tustin Unified School District is offering a six-week course designed to 
help parents build a stronger relationship with their children. 
</P>
<P>
 Dubbed "Active Parenting Today," the course will be held Wednesdays, Jan. 18 
to Feb. 22, from 7 to 9 p.m. at Barbara Benson Elementary School.It is open to 
parents with children ages 2 to 12. The fee is $15. 
</P>
<P>
 "This program will help parents instill in their children courage, 
responsibility, respect and cooperation," said Chris Wall, the district's 
parenting instructor. 
</P>
<P>
 The program involves discussion and sharing of experiences among the course 
participants in a classroom-like setting, Wall said. Sessions include training 
in parenting skills, child behavior, problem solving, parental roles in drug 
prevention and discipline. 
</P>
<P>
 Barbara Benson Elementary School is at 12712 Elizabeth Way. Information: (714) 
730-7336. BERT ELJERA 
