<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SOUTH COUNTY ; '55 ALIVE' PROGRAMS OFFERED OLDER DRIVERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior citizens can qualify for insurance discounts and improve their driving 
skills at low-cost driving clinics being held throughout South County in 
January. 
</P>
<P>
 Known as "55 Alive," the program is sponsored by the American Assn. of Retired 
Persons and participants must be at least age 50. Registration costs $8 and 
preregistration is required. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-day course focuses on helping seniors compensate for slowing reflexes 
and vision problems, along with updating attendees on Department of Motor 
Vehicles driving regulations. When the eight-hour course is completed, seniors 
are given certificates that can be sent to auto insurance companies for good 
driver discounts. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested in signing up must contact the facility where the class is 
being held. January classes in South County will be held: 
</P>
<P>
 * Monday, Jan. 9 and Tuesday, Jan. 10 from 9:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. at the San 
Clemente Senior Citizen Center, 242 Avenida del Mar in San Clemente. 
Information and registration: (714) 498-3322. 
</P>
<P>
 * Monday, Jan. 9 and Tuesday, Jan. 10 from 8 a.m. to noon at the Norman P. 
Murray Community and Senior Center, 24932 Oso Viejo Road in Mission Viejo. 
Information and registration: (714) 470-3062. 
</P>
<P>
 * Saturday, Jan. 14 and Saturday, Jan. 21 from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. at the Laguna 
Beach Senior Center in Lang Park at Westley and Coast Highway. Information and 
registration: (714) 497-2441. 
</P>
<P>
 * Wednesday, Jan. 18 and Wednesday, Jan. 25 from 9:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. at the 
Capistrano Bay Park and Recreation District, 34052 Del Obispo St. in Dana 
Point. Information and registration: (714) 496-4251. 
</P>
<P>
 * Wednesday, Jan. 19 and Thursday, Jan. 20 from noon to 4 p.m. at the Sea 
Country Senior Community Center, 24602 Aliso Creek Road. Information and 
registration: (714) 362-4342. 
</P>
<P>
 * Friday, Jan. 27 and Saturday, Jan. 28 from 12:30 to 4:30 p.m. at the Freedom 
Village Retirement Community, 23442 El Toro Road in Lake Forest. Information 
and registration: (714) 472-4700. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
