<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN ON PROBATION ARRESTED IN SHOOTING DEATH OF WIFE; CRIME: SUSPECT HAD BEEN 
ARRESTED FOR BATTERY IN 1993 DOMESTIC DISPUTE WITH 40-YEAR-OLD VICTIM, 
AUTHORITIES SAY. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man on probation for beating his wife shot her fatally after a domestic 
dispute, authorities alleged Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Victor Andrade, 57, of Pacoima, was being held on suspicion of murdering his 
wife, Maria, after he was questioned, Lt. Joseph Garcia said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have not yet established a motive for the slaying, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Andrade was spotted running from the death scene and was arrested about three 
blocks away, Garcia said. The couple lived in the 10900 block of Herrick 
Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The 40-year-old victim was shot twice in the upper torso, Garcia said. The 
suspect apparently fired several shots at his wife from arm's length, Garcia 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police seized a weapon they believe was used in the killing, Garcia said. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia said Andrade had been arrested for battery in a dispute with his wife 
in 1993. The man was still on probation from that incident, Garcia said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He served some days in jail," Garcia said. "I don't know how long." 
</P>
<P>
 The couple has four children, the oldest of whom is about 19 years old, police 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
