<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; WINNERS OF HOLIDAY BOAT PARADE NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Newport Harbor Area Chamber of Commerce has announced the winners of the 
1994 Newport Harbor Christmas Boat Parade. They will receive their trophies at 
a dinner and auction Jan. 20 at Le Meridien Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
 Unpretentious Too, owned by Geoff and Carol Landon of Balboa, won the 
Sweepstakes Award, according to Seymour Beek, a judging coordinator from the 
chamber's Commodores Division. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mayor's Award for Christmas theme went to skipper Bob Burns' Spirit of 
Newport. The Harbor Master's Award for the best display of humor went to Ebb 
Tide, owned by Gerald Van Vliet of San Juan Capistrano. 
</P>
<P>
 Tim Lewis' Zooter won the Judges' Award for originality. 
</P>
<P>
 Sasco Electric of Cerritos entered its El Navegante, which sailed off with the 
Commodores' Award for the best light display. 
</P>
<P>
 Balboa resident Koussay Okko got the Chairman's Award for holiday spirit for 
the display on Lattakia, and Alan and Susan Baron of Laguna Beach won the 
Dolphins Award for the best use of music on Magnanimous. 
</P>
<P>
 Three separate panels of six judges each viewed the parade each of three 
nights.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information on the awards dinner and auction, call (714) 729-4400. 
HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
