<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; MARCH OF DIMES FUND-RAISER SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The March of Dimes is soliciting walkers and pledges for its 25th annual 
WalkAmerica to raise money to fight birth defects. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 3,500 walkers raised $350,000 by walking the five-mile course 
through Huntington Beach this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers of the event hope to assemble 5,000 walkers and raise $500,000 in 
the 1995 walk, scheduled for April 29. 
</P>
<P>
 "Participants should know that 78% of the money they raise goes directly to 
research, education and community services and 60% of every dollar stays right 
here in Orange County to help Orange County's babies to be born healthy," event 
co-chairman Jim Hart said. 
</P>
<P>
 In its 24 years, WalkAmerica has raised $769 million nationwide for the March 
of Dimes. 
</P>
<P>
 "WalkAmerica accounts for almost half of the March of Dimes annual budget," 
Orange County executive director Lynette Carlucci said. 
</P>
<P>
 WalkAmerica 1995 will cover a five-mile course starting at Magnolia Avenue and 
Pacific Coast Highway at Huntington State Beach, walking north to Huntington 
Beach Pier and returning to the starting point. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about walking or pledging donations, call the March of 
Dimes at (714) 263-1100.HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
