 New York Comptroller's Office Joins Internet: The office announced it will 
become the first local government agency to make some of its financial 
information available to individuals through the worldwide computer network, 
city Comptroller Alan G. Hevesi said.The city joins FinanceNet, a user group 
designed to encourage the exchange of information on government finance. The 
comptroller's office can post audits, reports and other information for users 
of the Internet. Information provided by the comptroller's office can be found 
on "NYCCompNet." It is available through most Internet services using the 
gopher system and the address of gopher.financeNet.gov. 
