<P>
 Japan's Current Account Surplus Up 15% in November: The increase from the same 
month last year reversed a three-month decline, the Finance Ministry 
said.Still, the ministry said, the long-term trend points to a decreasing 
surplus in the current account, a measure of spending on nearly all goods and 
services. The November surplus was $9.67 billion. After adjusting for seasonal 
factors, that was 36% higher than October's figure, partly due to a jump in 
Japan's trade surplus, a key component of the current account. 
