<HEADLINE>
<P>
'RUSH' STORE BLAMES LOSS OF LEASE ON HIS DETRACTORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A vendor catering to fans of Rush Limbaugh is getting the bum's rush from an 
upscale shopping mall. 
</P>
<P>
 Current Events, which sells Limbaugh T-shirts, baseball caps, coffee mugs and 
"Rush Is Right" bumper stickers from a kiosk at Lane Avenue Shopping Center, 
will lose its lease when it expires Saturday, said owner Bill Khourie. 
</P>
<P>
 He blamed pressure from anti-Limbaugh forces who have picketed the mall 
recently. "It's tragic that this is happening, but I don't own the shopping 
center," Khourie said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Mall General Manager Marcy Starkey denied management was reacting to the 
handful of protesters. The decision not to renew the lease was part of a 
routine tenant evaluation, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Rosenberg, who led the protests, said: "We feel that the politics of 
divisiveness and hatred are bad business." 
</P>
<P>
 Neither Limbaugh nor his chief of staff, Kit Carson, was available to comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
