<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: SCHAEFER TAKES ON NEW JOB AT WESTERN FINANCIAL 
SAVINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joy Schaefer has been named senior executive vice president and chief 
operating officer of Western Financial Savings Bank in Irvine. She had been 
chief financial officer and treasurer of both the parent company, Westcorp, and 
the bank for the past three years. In addition, Lee Whatcott has been named 
senior vice president and chief financial officer of the bank. Whatcott had 
been controller of Westcorp and the bank for the past three years. Also, J. 
Keith Palmer was named treasurer, having served as assistant treasurer for the 
past year. 
</P>
<P>
 * Kathleen M. Gardarian has been elected to the board of Vans, an Orange shoe 
manufacturer, increasing the number of directors to nine. Gardarian is owner 
and president of Qualis International, an Irvine international trading and 
distribution company. 
</P>
<P>
 * Monica Florian has been installed as president of the Building Industry 
Assn.'s Orange County chapter. She succeeds 1993-94 president Bart Hansen of 
Shawntana Development. Florian is senior vice president of corporate affairs 
for Irvine Co. 
</P>
<P>
 * Thomas V. Joyce has been appointed to the new position of director of 
value-added services for Ingram Micro, a Santa Ana wholesale distributor of 
microcomputer products. Before joining the company, Joyce was vice president 
for operations support at EuroDisney. He also was a director in corporate 
finance for Walt Disney Co. 
</P>
<P>
 * Greg Anderson, a partner with Deloitte & Touche LLP, has moved his Health 
Systems Center of Expertise operation from Los Angeles to the Costa Mesa 
offices. The center provides consulting services to health care providers, 
insurers and managed-care organizations. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nancy Pagni has been appointed manager of the Northwest region office for 
DNA Labor Services in Santa Ana and its transportation affiliate, TLC Services. 
She will be based in the Tacoma, Wash., office. Pagni was previously with 
Superior Fast Freight for more than 15 years. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bernard Newman has joined Koll, an Irvine commercial real estate company, as 
director of the new facilities administrative services group, which provides 
clients with mail, distribution, reception, message center, conference room 
scheduling and shipping and receiving services. Newman was previously national 
marketing manager for Tascor, an Atlanta subsidiary of Norrell Corp. and IBM. 
He also spent 10 years with Pitney Bowes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
