<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE YEAR IN PICTURES; FAREWELLS AND FRESH STARTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It doesn't seem possible. Could all this have happened in one year? A 
President came home to be buried.So did a missing woman, whose grisly fate was 
finally uncovered. A mighty military base commenced its disappearance. So did a 
not-so-mighty football team. A wanted man's now infamous white Ford Bronco was 
spotted on a freeway in Irvine headed toward the most publicized trial in 
history. If fire-ravaged Laguna Beach neighborhoods, houses began to rise. But 
the county treasurer's house of cards collapsed, taking who knows how many 
people with it. Who will ever forget 1994? 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122994-0340 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 112422 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
December 29, 1994, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
